JD 9:

Major Accountabilities 

Translate global divisional category strategy into actionable sub-category strategies and implementation plans for Medical Affairs evidence generation, or adapt regional procurement strategies into country-specific execution plans.

Plan and lead sourcing initiatives for Real-World Evidence (RWE), Non-Interventional Studies (NIS), and Clinical Data Acquisition vendors, including CROs, data providers, and registries.

Define sourcing specifications, manage demand, and establish risk, compliance, and governance guardrails aligned with Medical Affairs standards.

Segment suppliers to identify strategic and critical relationships; lead annual business planning and innovation forums to improve data quality, delivery timelines, and cost effectiveness.

Manage strategic supplier performance using consistent KPIs and governance frameworks; proactively resolve performance risks and issues to ensure end-user satisfaction and compliance with Medical Affairs requirements.

Create, negotiate, and manage major contracts for the sub-category; ensure contract terms are clearly communicated and applied consistently across divisions and regions.

Oversee budget and resource allocation for the sub-category, ensuring effective spend stewardship aligned with Medical Affairs priorities and compliance expectations.

Develop and manage talent performance of direct reports; contribute to broader team capability building through coaching and knowledge sharing in evidence-generation procurement.

